<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1326] Inflater.end() method not always called in FieldsReader</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1326</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>
&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve just found an insidious memory leak in our own application as we did not always call Deflater.end() and Inflater.end(). As documented here;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=4797189&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=4797189&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The non-heap memory that the native zlib code uses is not freed in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FieldsWriter appears safe as no exception can be thrown between the Deflater&apos;s creation and end() as it uses a ByteArrayOutputStream&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FieldsReader, however, is not safe. In the event of a DataFormatException the call to end() will not occur.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12399551">LUCENE-1326</key>
            <summary>Inflater.end() method not always called in FieldsReader</summary>
